<main class="quiz-container">
  <h1>Personal Finance and Budgeting Quiz for College Students</h1>
  <form id="quiz-form">

    <div class="question">
      <p>Budgeting Basics: What is the primary purpose of creating a budget?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q1a" name="q1" value="a" />
        <label for="q1a">To track your spending habits</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q1b" name="q1" value="b" />
        <label for="q1b">To restrict your spending on entertainment</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q1c" name="q1" value="c" />
        <label for="q1c">To increase your income</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q1d" name="q1" value="d" />
        <label for="q1d">To invest in the stock market</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q1"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Savings and Emergency Funds: How much should you ideally save for an emergency fund?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q2a" name="q2" value="a" />
        <label for="q2a">The amount equivalent to 1 month of expenses</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q2b" name="q2" value="b" />
        <label for="q2b">The amount equivalent to 3-6 months of expenses</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q2c" name="q2" value="c" />
        <label for="q2c">$1000 regardless of expenses</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q2d" name="q2" value="d" />
        <label for="q2d">The same as your annual income</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q2"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Understanding Credit: What is a credit report?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q3a" name="q3" value="a" />
        <label for="q3a">A monthly statement of your credit card expenses</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q3b" name="q3" value="b" />
        <label for="q3b">A record of your investments</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q3c" name="q3" value="c" />
        <label for="q3c">A detailed report of your credit history</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q3d" name="q3" value="d" />
        <label for="q3d">A plan for future credit use</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q3"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Student Loans and Debt Management: Which of the following is a strategy for managing student loan debt?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q4a" name="q4" value="a" />
        <label for="q4a">Paying only the interest on the loan</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q4b" name="q4" value="b" />
        <label for="q4b">Using a credit card to pay off student loans</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q4c" name="q4" value="c" />
        <label for="q4c">Consolidating multiple federal student loans into one</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q4d" name="q4" value="d" />
        <label for="q4d">Ignoring the loan until you secure a high-paying job</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q4"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Investing Basics for Students: What does diversification in investing mean?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q5a" name="q5" value="a" />
        <label for="q5a">Investing all your money in one stock</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q5b" name="q5" value="b" />
        <label for="q5b">Spreading your investments across different types of assets</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q5c" name="q5" value="c" />
        <label for="q5c">Keeping all your money in a savings account</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q5d" name="q5" value="d" />
        <label for="q5d">Borrowing money to invest</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q5"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Smart Spending Tips: What is a significant benefit of cooking at home rather than eating out frequently?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q6a" name="q6" value="a" />
        <label for="q6a">It is more time-consuming</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q6b" name="q6" value="b" />
        <label for="q6b">It offers more variety</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q6c" name="q6" value="c" />
        <label for="q6c">It is generally cheaper and healthier</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q6d" name="q6" value="d" />
        <label for="q6d">It requires less planning</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q6"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Understanding Taxes: What is a W-2 form used for?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q7a" name="q7" value="a" />
        <label for="q7a">To report income from freelance work</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q7b" name="q7" value="b" />
        <label for="q7b">To summarize annual earnings and taxes withheld by an employer</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q7c" name="q7" value="c" />
        <label for="q7c">To apply for tax return</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q7d" name="q7" value="d" />
        <label for="q7d">To declare independence from parents for tax purposes</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q7"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Introduction to Insurance: What is a deductible?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q8a" name="q8" value="a" />
        <label for="q8a">The maximum amount an insurance company will pay for a covered claim under the policy</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q8b" name="q8" value="b" />
        <label for="q8b">Circumstances that are not covered by the insurance policy</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q8c" name="q8" value="c" />
        <label for="q8c">The amount you pay out of pocket</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q8d" name="q8" value="d" />
        <label for="q8d">The amount you pay to the insurance company to keep your policy active</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q8"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Budgeting Basics: When creating a budget, what is important to include?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q9a" name="q9" value="a" />
        <label for="q9a">Only fixed expenses like rent</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q9b" name="q9" value="b" />
        <label for="q9b">A category for savings</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q9c" name="q9" value="c" />
        <label for="q9c">Unpredictable expenses only</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q9d" name="q9" value="d" />
        <label for="q9d">Luxuries and entertainment exclusively</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q9"></p>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <p>Investing Basics for Students: Why is it recommended to start investing early?</p>
      <div class="options">
        <input type="radio" id="q10a" name="q10" value="a" />
        <label for="q10a">To immediately use up all your savings</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q10b" name="q10" value="b" />
        <label for="q10b">For the potential benefits of compound interest over time</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q10c" name="q10" value="c" />
        <label for="q10c">Because it's easier than working</label><br />
        <input type="radio" id="q10d" name="q10" value="d" />
        <label for="q10d">To avoid learning about personal finance</label>
      </div>
      <p class="feedback" id="feedback-q10"></p>
    </div>


    <button type="submit">Submit Answers</button>
  </form>
</main>